The paper deals with processing cross-modal input, specifically linguistic instructions and visual perception, to segment objects and associate them with high-level concepts. This involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques, which are covered in the cs.CL and cs.CV sub-categories respectively. The paper also presents a method for learning from small datasets, which falls under the purview of machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), covered by the cs.AI sub-category. The experiments involve a table-top object manipulation scenario, which suggests the use of robotics (cs.RO) and possibly reinforcement learning (RL) techniques. Finally, the paper deals with learning and generalization, which are core topics in the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
